def: Fossil fruit; a fruit petrified; a carpolite.
The bar of a carriage to which the traces are fastened; thewhiffletree.

To refit; to repair, or make reparation for; hence, to repay orrequite. [Obs.]It shall be good that you redub that negligence. Wyatt.God shall give power to redub it with some like requital to theFrench. Grafton.
Not sexual; not proper or peculiar to one of the sexes. DeQuincey.
The wax-covered fruit of the wax myrtle, or bayberry. SeeBayberry, and Candleberry tree.
A prefix meaning pertaining to, produced by, or in some wayconnected with, magnetism.

Having the characteristics of Circe, daughter of Sol andPerseis, a mythological enchantress, who first charmed her victimsand then changed them to the forms of beasts; pleasing, but noxious;as, a Circean draught.
Gay; merry; sprightly; joyous; glad; cheerful; as, a blithespirit.The blithe sounds of festal music. Prescott.A daughter fair, So buxom, blithe, and debonair. Milton.
